data.enText: take off clothes

data.chText: 脱光衣服；脱掉大部分衣服；扒光…的衣服
data.enText: to take off all or most of your clothes or another person's clothes

data.chText: 我脱掉衣服，把全身洗了洗。
data.enText: I stripped and washed myself all over.

data.chText: 我们脱掉衣服，跑进水里。
data.enText: We stripped off and ran down to the water.

data.chText: 她把衣服脱得只剩下了内衣。
data.enText: She stripped down to her underwear.

data.chText: 他脱光了上衣站在那里。
data.enText: He stood there stripped to the waist (= he had no clothes on the upper part of his body) .

data.chText: 他被扒得一丝不挂，丢在一间牢房里。
data.enText: He was stripped naked and left in a cell.

data.chText: 进行脱衣表演；表演脱衣舞
data.enText: to take off your clothes as a form of entertainment; to perform a striptease
remove layer

data.chText: 除去，剥去（一层）；（尤指）剥光
data.enText: to remove a layer from sth, especially so that it is completely exposed

data.chText: 把现有的油漆全部刮掉。
data.enText: Strip off all the existing paint.
Deer had stripped the tree of its bark.
Deer had stripped all the bark off the tree.

data.chText: 客人走后，我把被单床单全都撤了下来。
data.enText: After the guests had gone, I stripped all the beds (= removed all the sheets in order to wash them) .
remove everything

data.chText: 从（某处）拿走所有东西；使（某处）空无一物
data.enText: to remove all the things from a place and leave it empty

data.chText: 我们不得不将原有的线路全部拆除，从头再来。
data.enText: We had to strip out all the old wiring and start again.
Thieves had stripped the house bare.
machine
to separate a machine, etc. into parts so that they can be cleaned or repaired

data.chText: 他们教我们拆卸、安装汽车引擎。
data.enText: They taught us how to strip down a car engine and put it back together again.
punishment
to take away property or honours from sb, as a punishment

data.chText: 他名誉扫地，被取消了头衔。
data.enText: He was disgraced and stripped of his title.

to remove a layer from sth

data.chText: 首先，你得把原来的灰泥全部刮掉。
data.enText: First, you need to strip away all the old plaster.

data.chText: 这部电影旨在揭穿有关肯尼迪生平的种种谎言。

tr: a form of erotic entertainment in which a dancer gradually undresses to music
example: she did a strip right in front of everyone

artifact consisting of a narrow flat piece of material
thin piece of wood or metal
a sequence of drawings telling a story in a newspaper or comic book
a relatively long narrow piece of something
example: he felt a flat strip of muscle
please don't undress in front of everybody!
She strips in front of strangers every night for a living
The nurse quickly undressed the accident victim

He disinvested himself of his garments

example: The boys cleaned the sandwich platters
The trees were cleaned of apples by the storm

value.def: A strip of something such as paper, cloth, or food is a long, narrow piece of it.

example.ex: ...a new kind of manufactured wood made by pressing strips of wood together and baking them...
example.tran: 一种用木条压紧并烘烤而制成的新型人造木材

example.ex: The simplest rag-rugs are made with strips of fabric plaited together...
example.tran: 最简单的碎布地毯是由碎布条编在一起制成的。

example.ex: Serve dish with strips of fresh raw vegetables.
example.tran: 用新鲜的生蔬菜条作配菜。

value.def: A strip of land or water is a long narrow area of it.

example.ex: The coastal cities of Liguria sit on narrow strips of land lying under steep mountains.
example.tran: 利古里亚的沿海城市坐落在陡峭山脉下的狭长地带上。

example.ex: ...a short boat ride across a narrow strip of water.
example.tran: 乘船渡过一小段狭窄的带状水域。

value.tran: 狭长区域;带状(陆地、水域)

value.def: A strip is a long street in a city or town, where there are a lot of stores, restaurants, and hotels.

example.ex: ...Goff's Charcoal Hamburgers on Lover's Lane, a busy commercial strip in North Dallas.
example.tran: 位于北达拉斯的一条名为“情人巷”的繁华商业街上的戈夫炭烤汉堡店

value.def: If you strip, you take off your clothes.

example.ex: They stripped completely, and lay in the damp grass...
example.tran: 他们脱光衣服，躺在潮湿的草地上。

example.ex: Women residents stripped naked in protest.
example.tran: 女性居民裸体以示抗议。

example.ex: The children were brazenly stripping off and leaping into the sea.
example.tran: 孩子们正无所顾忌地脱光衣服跳进海里。

value.def: If someone is stripped, their clothes are taken off by another person, for example in order to search for hidden or illegal things.

example.ex: One prisoner claimed he'd been dragged to a cell, stripped and beaten.
example.tran: 一名犯人声称他曾被拖进一间牢房，全身被脱光并遭到毒打。

value.def: To strip something means to remove everything that covers it.

example.ex: After Mike left for work I stripped the beds and vacuumed the carpets...
example.tran: 迈克去上班后，我扯下了床罩并用吸尘器清扫地毯。

example.ex: The floorboards in both this room and the dining room have been stripped, sanded and sealed.
example.tran: 这个房间和餐厅的木地板都已经被刮除涂层并进行了打磨上蜡。

value.def: If you strip an engine or a piece of equipment, you take it to pieces so that it can be cleaned or repaired.

example.ex: Volvo's three-man team stripped the car and restored it.
example.tran: 沃尔沃公司的 3 人小组将车拆开进行了维修。

example.ex: In five years I had to strip the water pump down four times...
example.tran: 5 年来我不得不将水泵拆开了 4 次。

example.ex: I stripped down the two SU carburettors, cleaned and polished the pieces and rebuilt the units.
example.tran: 我将这两个SU汽化器拆卸开，把各个零件清洗擦亮后重新组装起来。

value.def: To strip someone of their property, rights, or titles means to take those things away from them.

example.ex: The soldiers have stripped the civilians of their passports, and every other type of document...
example.tran: 士兵们已经夺走了平民的护照以及所有其他类型的证件。

example.ex: A senior official was stripped of all his privileges for publicly criticising his employer.
example.tran: 一名高管由于公然批评其老板而被剥夺了所有特权。

value.tran: 剥夺，褫夺(财产、权利、头衔)

value.def: In a newspaper or magazine, a strip is a series of drawings which tell a story. The words spoken by the characters are often written on the drawings.

example.ex: ...the Doonesbury strip.
example.tran: 杜尼斯伯理政治漫画

value.def: If you tear a strip off someone or if you tear them off a strip, you speak to them angrily and criticize them severely.

example.ex: He heard Nora tearing a strip off an orderly for not returning the food bins to the kitchen soon enough...
example.tran: 他听到诺拉正在破口大骂一名勤务兵没有将食品箱及时送回厨房。

example.ex: When the police arrived to tear him off a strip he apologised for all the trouble he'd caused them.
example.tran: 当警察赶到把他狠狠地教训了一番后，他为自己给他们带来的所有麻烦表示道歉。

value.tran: 怒斥;痛骂;把…骂得狗血淋头
